  "readme": "<p>\n\tTo start using ONLYOFFICE Docs with Nextcloud or ownCloud, you have to install the respective app and enable the ONLYOFFICE plugin in either app.\n</p>\n<p>\n\tThe address to the document server has to be configured inside the plugin. Pleaes note that the parameter <b>documentserver</b> is the name (FQDN, without a port number) of the server with the ONLYOFFICE Docs installed. The address must be accessible for the user browser and from the respective Nextcloud or ownCloud server. The server address must also be accessible from ONLYOFFICE Docs for operating correctly.\n</p>\n<pre>\n    https://&lt;documentserver&gt;/onlyoffice-documentserver\n</pre>\n<h3>\n\tConfiguration of ONLYOFFICE plugin in Nextcloud\n</h3>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tLogin to Nextcloud as user <i>Administrator</i>.\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tGoto <i>Apps</i> \u2192 <i>Office &amp; Text</i> \u2192 enable <i>ONLYOFFICE</i>.\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tGoto <i>Admin</i> settings and look for <i>ONLYOFFICE</i>. There enter the address above
  "readme_appliance": "<p>\n\tThis app appliance already includes ONLYOFFICE Document Server and ownCloud.\n</p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tPlease make sure you access UCS and ownCloud via https://&lt;hostname&gt;.&lt;ucs-domain&gt; and not with the IP address.\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tPlease accept an exception for the UCS SSL certificate.\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tThe communication between ownCloud and ONLYOFFICE uses hostnames. If the above &lt;hostname&gt;.&lt;ucs-domain&gt; combination does not work for your client, you can either add the UCS system to your client's list of DNS nameservers or you can add the IP address and the hostname to your local hosts file.\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\tThe login credentials for the ownCloud admin user are:\n</p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tusername: owncloud\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tpassword: owncloud\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\tPlease change the password for the owncloud admin user!\n</p>",

  "readme_en": "<p>\n\tTo start using ONLYOFFICE Docs with Nextcloud or ownCloud, you have to install the respective app and enable the ONLYOFFICE plugin in either app.\n</p>\n<p>\n\tThe address to the document server has to be configured inside the plugin. Pleaes note that the parameter <b>documentserver</b> is the name (FQDN, without a port number) of the server with the ONLYOFFICE Docs installed. The address must be accessible for the user browser and from the respective Nextcloud or ownCloud server.
